 From the Makoy Diner opening to a night of song and dance at Divas of Dance, check out a gallery of what Port Elizabethans got up to in the past week.


			
				
			
				
				Guests, from left, Mimi Rupp, Loudeaux Minnie, Ranier Minnie and Petra Palframan sampled the new menu at Makoy Fast Food Diner which opened in  Walmer last Wednesday Picture: Louise Liebernberg 

				
			
				
			
				
				Bay singer Vuyiseka ‘LoveChild’ Maguga, left, and her grandmother Nombulelo Maguga at the  launch of the video of her  debut single ‘Khaw’buye’ at the  Athenaeum in Central  Picture:  Londeka Dlamini
				
			
				
			
				
				Jude Ganasen, left, and Dominic Hurd from the Durban based band Easy Freak, who performed at Food Truck Friday’s 1st Birthday Picture: Kgosi Motsepe
				
			
				
			
				
				BLC attorneys director Sonja Tifloen, front, and Jose Korkie had  fun at the Divas of Dance concert held at the Boardwalk on Friday night
 Picture: Londeka Dlamini
				
			
				
			
				
				Captain of the MS Albatros, Robert Fronenbroek, left, welcomes on board Transnet National Ports Authority acting port manager Captain Faisal Sultan and corporate affairs manager Margorie Makama. The cruise ship arrived on Monday at the port of Port Elizabeth

				
			
				
			
				
				Kirk West, Jill Sneesby, centre, and Janice Giddy were at the opening of the Images of India exhibition at Sneesby’s home in Walmer last Friday. Many of the images on display were taken during a photographic tour that Sneesby conducted to India at the beginning of the year   Picture: Louise Liebenberg
				
			
				
			
				
				Kitibella online shoe shop owner Nadine Murray and Gerhard Theys were at the Boardwalk for the Divas of Dance concert last Friday 
Picture: Londeka Dlamini

				
			
				
			
				
